ce:section.ce:para:
In this work, we provide a facile and feasible electrospinning approach to prepare portable and stable SQDs-based sensor from aqueous mixture of poly(vinyl alcohol) (PVA) and SQDs (Fig. 1
                     ). The prepared PVA/SQDs composite film displayed strong and stable solid-state fluorescence in response to photo-oxidation and environmental changes, which is ascribed to the stabilization by PVA. Moreover, the PVA/SQDs film exhibited responsive fluorescence quenching behavior towards Fe3
                     +, so it has the potential to be utilized as a film sensor to detect Fe3+. To our knowledge, this is the first example of a portable SQDs-based solid sensor constructed using electrospinning technology.
